                <h3>Reduce Your Debt</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Pay off credit cards with the highest minimum payments first (avalanche method targets interest, snowball targets smallest balances)</li>
                    <li>Refinance auto or student loans for a lower monthly payment — extending the term reduces DTI even if total interest is higher</li>
                    <li>Consolidate multiple debts into one lower-payment loan</li>
                    <li>Avoid taking on new debt (new car, personal loan) before applying for a mortgage</li>
                    <li>Pay down credit card balances below 30% of limits — this also boosts your credit score</li>
